flag.brine

Physical properties of brine.

flag.brine.bulk_modulus(P: FVec, T: FVec, Sa: FVec, NaCl: FVec, KCl: FVec, CaCl2: FVec, model: str = 'rpl') → FVec

Bulk modulus of brine [GPa].

Application conditions:

  1. Pressure [MPa] : 0 <= P <= 140

  2. Temperature [C] : 0 <= T <= 300

  3. Salinity [ppm] : 0 <= Sa <= 300,000

Parameters:

  • P (TFVec) – Pressure [MPa]

  • T (TFVec) – Temperature [C]

  • Sa (TFVec) – Salinity [ppm]

  • NaCl (TFVec) – Weight percent of NaCl of total salt of brine [%].

  • KCl (TFVec) – Weight percent of KCl of total salt of brine [%].

  • CaCl2 (TFVec) – Weight percent of CaCl2 of total salt of brine [%].

  • model (str) – Model used to calculate bulk modulus. Defaults to ‘rpl’.

Returns:

Bulk modulus of pure water [km/s].

Return type:

TFVec

flag.brine.gas_solubility(P: FVec, T: FVec, Sa: FVec, model: str = 'rpl') → FVec

Solubility of petroleum gas in brine.

Application conditions:

  1. Pressure [MPa] : 6.895 <= P <= 68.948

  2. Temperature [C] : 0 <= T <= Vapor point

  3. Salinity [ppm] : 0 <= Sa <= 300,000

Parameters:

  • P (TFVec) – Pressure [MPa]

  • T (TFVec) – Temperature [C]

  • T – Salinity [ppm]

  • model (str) – Model used to calculate solubility. Defaults to ‘rpl’.

Returns:

Solubility of petroleum gas in brine.

Return type:

TFVec

flag.brine.resistivity(T: FVec, Sa: FVec, model: str = 'rpl') → FVec

Resistivity of brine [cP].

  1. Temperature [C] : 0 <= T <= 300

  2. Salinity [ppm] : 0 <= Sa <= 300,000

Model details:

From Western Atlas. (1995)

Parameters:

  • Sa (TFVec) – Salinity [ppm]

  • model (str) – Model used to calculate viscosity. Defaults to ‘rpl’.

Returns:

Viscosity of pure water [cP].

Return type:

TFVec
